    <p>Here's what 130 grams of protein looks like in a day — using real food most men already eat, spread across four simple eating occasions.</p>

    <p>If you've already seen <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/what-120g-protein-looks-like/">what 120 grams of protein looks like</a>, you know that three solid meals gets most men close to the baseline. 130g is the next step — the number where muscle preservation starts to feel less like effort and more like a consistent habit.</p>

    <p>The difference between 120g and 130g is not another meal. It's one small addition — a cup of cottage cheese, an extra egg, or a slightly larger dinner portion. But seeing what that looks like in practice is what makes it stick.</p>

    <div class="killer-line">
      120g stops the bleeding.<br><span>130g is where you start to hold ground.</span>
    </div>

